Maggie is a 93-year-old widow (used to be an elementary school teacher) who has lived a modest and financially responsible life. 
She receives income from Social Security, a teacher’s pension, and retirement savings. 
While she is not highly tech-savvy, she owns a tablet that she uses for email, video calls with family, and basic browsing. 
Her grandson helped her download the financial tracking app.

She values independence and wants to remain in control of her finances without relying entirely on her children.
She want to be able to easiler monitor retirement funds to ensure they last, save and organize mopney she hopes to pass on to her grandchildren, and avoid scam charges. 

*Low to moderate technology comfort level

User Stories:

As a user that isn't super confident in technology, I want a system that is very easy to use and understand with clear instructions.

As an aging user, I want the ability to increase the size of the text so that I can easily read it.
Wants: 
- Large readable text
- Simple dashboard showing only the things she needs
- Alerts for unusual activity
